documentProperties.name: AllowWebPlayerResume
documentProperties.description: A web client setting where you can allow users to resume at the last known state when they are launching a previously opened analysis.

documentProperties.name: MaxMissingTimeParts
documentProperties.description: Specifies the maximum number of time parts to insert when compensating for missing time series values.

documentProperties.name: FiscalYearOffset
documentProperties.description:
Specifies the number of months from the start of the calendar year to the start of the fiscal year.
For instance, a value of -1 specifies that the fiscal year starts in December of the previous calendar year, whereas a value of 2 specifies that it starts in March of the current calendar year.
